              <OfferCard key={o.title} offer={o} />
            ))}
          </div>

          <div className="mt-12 rounded-3xl border border-zinc-200 bg-zinc-50 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <div className="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 md:items-start">
              <div>
                <p className="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-950">Doctrine Statement</p>
                <p className="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-zinc-700">
                There is a fair amount of complexity across fitness, firearms, home defense, and
                insurance, but my approach is deliberately simple. I rely heavily on the KISS
                method—Keep It Simple, Stupid. I believe that if you truly understand a subject, you
                should be able to explain it to a five-year-old and still get the point across.
                Complexity does not equal competence; clarity does.
                <br /><br />
                I am not a Tier 1 operator, nor do I trade in exaggerated claims or theatrics. I am an
                experienced Soldier, Military Police professional, leader, and coach who has spent a
                long career in the security sector and an equally long time in military service. My
                focus is calm decision-making, responsibility, and repeatable processes that work
                under stress.
                <br /><br />
                On the fitness side, I was formerly NASM certified. What I do maintain is applied knowledge, coaching experience, and
                results earned through years of real-world use. My coaching places a heavy emphasis
                on diet and nutrition, because training fails quickly when fuel and recovery are
                ignored.
                <br /><br />
                On the firearms and security side, I have 10+ years in the Missouri National Guard,
                serving my entire career as Military Police, with four deployments and two state
                emergency duties. I am trained in active shooter response, versed in the Run, Hide,
                Fight procedure, and experienced in Detainee Operations, Quick Response Force (QRF),
                and Customs & Border Clearance. Instruction remains civilian-appropriate and
                safety-focused at all times.
              </p>
              </div>
              <div className="rounded-3xl border border-zinc-200 bg-white p-6">
                <p className="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-950">Who this is not for</p>
                <ul className="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-zinc-700">
                  <li className="flex gap-2"><CheckCircle2 className="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4" />People chasing aesthetics over capability</li>
                  <li className="flex gap-2"><CheckCircle2 className="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4" />Anyone looking for influencer workouts or hype-based programming</li>
                  <li className="flex gap-2"><CheckCircle2 className="mt-0.5 h-4 w-4" />Those unwilling to train consistently when conditions are not ideal</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      {/* Firearms */}
      <section id="firearms" className="border-t border-zinc-200 bg-white">
        <div className="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-14 sm:px-6 sm:py-20">
          <SectionHeader
            kicker="Firearm instruction"
            title="Build safe skill"
            subtitle="Instruction centered on safety, responsibility, and fundamentals. The goal is confidence without recklessness."
          />

          <div className="mt-10 grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">
